author: Murabel Pretzel
text:
Takeomi looked into dark eyes that seemed to see through him and his worries before looking away to stare into the distance.

"Yeah. It's nothing."

author: Murabel Pretzel
text: The curious glint in Shinichiro's eyes wasn't left unnoticed by Takeomi but he refused to say that he was worried about the Sano's fortune.

author: Murabel Pretzel
text:
the one who suggested to go fortune telling, himself.

"Everything alright?"

Shinichiro bumped their shoulders together, successfully pulling Takeomi out from his thoughts.

author: Murabel Pretzel
text: Shinichiro grinned at his childhood best friend and vice captain. The lady was full of bull. He turned to look at the others from their class. They all seemed to be having fun. Everyone seemed to be having fun besides Takeomi,

author: Murabel Pretzel
text:
ShinOmi :p

Takeomi knew that the lady could just be lying like every other person in the fortune telling industry. But for some reason, he feels dread pooling at the bottom of his stomach. He swallows shallowly, sweat forming on his face as he thinks back to her words.
